value.title: Check’s in the mail: Trump offering government aid, including cash, in weeks before the election
value.excerpt: In recent days, President Donald Trump has promised millions of Medicare recipients that — thanks to him — they’ll soon be getting an “incredible” $200 card in the mail to help them pay for prescriptions.

value.title: EXCLUSIVE: VP Mike Pence tells Channel 2 President Trump won Tuesday’s debate ‘outright’
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence is defending President Donald Trump’s performance following Tuesday night’s controversial debate and says he believes Trump won. Channel 2′s Richard Elliot spoke exclusively with Pence following his appearance at the Faith and Freedom Coalition conference that was held Wednesday at the Cobb Galleria Centre.

value.title: Intelligence Officials Urged Trump Spy Chief Not to Disclose Unverified Russian Claims About Clinton
value.excerpt: Officials at the Central Intelligence Agency and National Security Agency feared that sharing the information with Congress would give credence to unsubstantiated Kremlin-backed material.

value.title: Trump signs spending bill to keep government open until December 11
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump early Thursday morning signed a spending bill to keep the government open until December 11, according to a tweet from White House spokesman Judd Deere.

value.title: Trump denies knowing who 'Proud Boys' are, again declines to condemn white supremacy by name
value.excerpt: President Trump on Wednesday claimed he doesn't know who the Proud Boys are, told the group to "stand down," and again declined to condemn white supremacy by name.

value.title: Trump, Biden continue sniping during Midwest campaigning: ‘He will destroy our Country!' vs. ‘a national embarrassment’
value.excerpt: Donald Trump and Joe Biden continued their debate-stage clash from afar on Wednesday as they competed for working-class voters in the Midwest.

value.title: Trump falsely claims 'poll watchers' blocked from observing early voting sites in Philadelphia
value.excerpt: President Trump falsely claimed that "poll watchers" were blocked from entering early voting locations in Philadelphia, an issue his campaign and the RNC are litigating.

value.title: Former Trump campaign manager Brad Parscale steps down from role as senior adviser
value.excerpt: Brad Parscale stepped down from his role as a senior adviser to President Donald Trump's campaign on Wednesday, two sources close to the campaign confirmed to CNN.

value.title: Second lady Karen Pence makes 3 veteran-themed stops in Jacksonville area
value.excerpt: Karen Pence, wife of Vice President Mike Pence, made three stops in Jacksonville, focused on veterans' issues.

value.title: Biden, Mr. Rogers' widow Joanne hold virtual call during Pennsylvania campaign stop
value.excerpt: Rogers, 92, is an outspoken critic of President Trump and supporter of the Biden campaign.

value.title: Sen. Chuck Grassley: 'I'd be very concerned' about how Donald Trump's tax returns got out
value.excerpt: Asked about the substance of the New York Times' reporting that Trump paid $750 in income tax in 2016 and 2017, Grassley said he doesn't have enough evidence.

value.title: Trump returns to campaign trail with Minnesota rally after widely panned debate
value.excerpt: Trump and his campaign see Minnesota as a special project, their best chance to flip a state Hillary Clinton won in 2016. Biden is leading in polls.

value.title: Joe Biden’s ObamaCare Tax Avoidance
value.excerpt: In 2019 he and his wife legally dodged payroll levies on $228,703 in income.

value.title: Federal judge refuses to stop mail-in voting in Montana, blasts Trump-backed 'fiction' of massive voter fraud
value.excerpt: A federal judge in Montana rejected the Trump campaign's effort to stop an expansion of mail-in voting in the state.

value.title: Trump has repeatedly been endorsed by white supremacist groups and other far-right extremists, and they've looked to him as a source of encouragement
value.excerpt: Trump's refusal to explicitly condemn white supremacist groups during Tuesday night's debate follows a similar pattern.

value.title: Wisconsin gov tells Trump to require masks at state rallies — or skip them
value.excerpt: Gov. Tony Evers suggested President Trump not come to Wisconsin for two campaign rallies this weekend, as the state struggles with record-breaking numbers of hospitalizations and new coronavirus cases.

value.title: Biden kicks off train tour through Ohio, Pennsylvania after raucous debate
value.excerpt: Joe Biden is embarking on a roughly 200-mile train tour on Wednesday through Ohio and Pennsylvania, appealing to voters who have strayed from Democrats in recent years.

value.title: Trump says he doesn't know who Proud Boys are, says 'let law enforcement do their work'
value.excerpt: President Trump on Wednesday tried to clear up confusion after telling the right-wing men’s group the Proud Boys to “stand back and stand by,” saying he didn’t know who the group was but they should let law enforcement do their job.

value.title: Chicago Mayor Lightfoot slams Trump after he blasts Windy City violence
value.excerpt: Democratic Chicago Mayor Lori Lightfoot fired back at President Trump on Tuesday night after he skewered her city during a presidential campaign debate against Joe Biden as a hotbed of crime and violence.

value.title: Biden says at debate he doesn't support Green New Deal, but his campaign website calls it 'crucial framework'
value.excerpt: Joe Biden said Tuesday night at the first presidential debate that he does not support the Green New Deal, but his campaign website calls it a “crucial framework” for meeting climate change challenges.

value.title: Former Playboy Playmate Karen McDougal says she’s ‘been forgiven by Jesus’ for alleged Trump affair
value.excerpt: During the 2016 election, National Enquirer parent company American Media Inc. paid McDougal $150,000 for the rights to her story, which it never published. The company eventually acknowledged the purchase was a “catch-and-kill” maneuver to boost Trump's presidential prospects.
